course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 200 degrees. Pick @basil{1%ounce} leaves from stems. Discard stems. Peel and halve @cucumber{1} lengthwise, then thinly slice into half-moons. Thinly slice @fresh mozzarella{8%ounce}.

Pile one @flatbreads{4%unit} with mozzarella, @prosciutto{4%ounce}, and basil leaves. Top with other flatbread. Cut stack in half widthwise. Repeat with other two flatbreads.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add panini. Cook until golden brown and cheese has melted, ~{3-4%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #baking sheet{}, and place in oven to keep warm. Repeat with remaining panini, and add more olive oil if necessary.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @grape tomatoes{8%ounce}(halved), @mixed greens{4%ounce}, and cucumbers with @balsamic vinegar{2%tablespoon} and a large drizzle of olive oil. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Serve: Cut the creamy prosciutto panini into triangles, and serve with green salad on the side. Enjoy!

> Although we're calling this a panini, it's basically a grilled cheese - the entire family will LOVE it!
> The sandwich is hearty thanks to the Italian ham, flavorful thanks to the herbs, and oh-so-creamy.
